>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Recycling dungeons to save the top end game?</span><hr size=1> On every server in EverQuest there is a group of people who are on the &quot;leading edge&quot;. Depending on circumstances there are anywhere from 50 to several hundred of them per server. They were the first people to level to 50. They were first to kill Naggy and Vox. They were the first people to venture to the planes and to take down gods. When Kunark was released, they raced to level 60. They were the first people to enter Howling Stones and Sebilis. The first to kill Trakanon, Venril Sathir and the Kunark dragons. They entered and conquered Veeshan's Peak before anyone else on the server. Soon after Velious' release they were clearing the Arena and PoG to get the &quot;basic&quot; Velious armor, then they moved to ToV and were the first people to acquire the &quot;advanced&quot; Velious armors. Then it was on to the Velious dragons, the first brood and eventually, Sleeper's and NToV.<br>
<br>
Because these people are always doing these things &quot;first&quot;, they have no competition for them and thus, they can schedule their raids whenever it is convenient without the worry that someone else will &quot;beat them to the spawn&quot;. The irony of course, is that these &quot;uber&quot; people don't NEED to be able to schedule their raids. They're on-line frequently enough and for large enough blocks of time that they usually win the race to contested spawns anyway. And don't get me wrong, I don't hate these people or feel the need to belittle them - they just have different circumstances in their lives that allow them to commit a lot of time to EQ.<br>
<br>
I blame Verant for cutting off my access to high-end encounters. VI has made a fundamental blunder in their design of the high-end game. They have failed to allow for the fact that the EQ population has &quot;matured&quot;. There are now thousands of level 60ish people who are potentially capable of participating in these encounters on each server rather than the few hundred that were when Velious first came out.<br>
<br>
Verant has designed things so that items enter each server at a constant rate &quot;per server&quot;. I would encourage them to re-examine this design choice. Uber mobs should spawn at a rate that reflects the size of the population able to kill it instead of at a rate designed to limit item flow to X per week per server. <br>
<br>
They should also figure out a method to &quot;spread the opportunity&quot; a bit more. Simply increasing the spawn rates on uber mobs will mainly result in the people that get most of the kills on them now to get even more of the kills (unless they gave them respawn times measured in minutes or a few hours, which would lead to massive mudflation).<br>
<br>
My personal favorite would be to leave the current natural spawn times pretty much un-changed, but to also add some ways for uber mobs to be triggered by a group at a time of their own choosing. Perhaps create quests to enable this or some rare loot &quot;spawn tokens&quot; that would drop off of random mobs throughout Norrath. This would allow people that need to schedule their EQ time the opportunity to experience more of the high end content while still allowing &quot;uber guilds&quot; to race to mobs at server up and not have to worry about doing spawn token quests or to have to find rare drop spawn token items.<br>
<br>
-Asron<br>
Emerald Templars Guild<br>
Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=22318.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=22318.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22318.topic&index=30><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=22318.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=22318.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22318.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22318.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies